Over There,” George M. Cohan’s rousing World War I anthem, captures much of the Western church’s perception of missions over the last century.
Nowadays, our “here” increasingly resembles foreign territory, as the Western church finds itself on the social and cultural margins.
How does that background inform your writing on the challenges facing the Western church today?
I had grown up in a Christian family, walked away from the faith, gone to university, and grown very ambitious in a worldly way.
